The authors of the open letter are convinced that a tightening of the law on private arms owners will not prevent criminals from operating on the black market.
At the moment, according to the authors in Moscow, any weapon can be found for little money.
Meanwhile, the Ministry of the Interior stresses that the spread of illegal weapons is under control.
Suppliers: from the factories to the officers
The weapons reach the black market via several channels.
There are five such main channels, a former Colonel Viktor Baranez, who worked for ten years in the Ministry of Education and the General Staff.
Screenshot of a website that takes arms orders
The first channel is the army or the military, i.e. weapons that were stolen during the fighting in the Caucasus.
